[
  {
    "end_time": 3326,
    "index": 1,
    "start_time": 335,
    "text": "Scientific American Instant Egghead"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 7007,
    "index": 2,
    "start_time": 5094,
    "text": "You&#39;ve probably heard \ndifferent explanations"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 8852,
    "index": 3,
    "start_time": 7007,
    "text": "for why leaves change color:"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 10406,
    "index": 4,
    "start_time": 8852,
    "text": "lower temperatures,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 11862,
    "index": 5,
    "start_time": 10406,
    "text": "less daylight,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 13178,
    "index": 6,
    "start_time": 11862,
    "text": "less rain."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 14997,
    "index": 7,
    "start_time": 13178,
    "text": "But, the correct answer is"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 16428,
    "index": 8,
    "start_time": 14997,
    "text": "less daylight."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 18748,
    "index": 9,
    "start_time": 16428,
    "text": "Temperature can affect\nthe intensity of leaf color,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 20428,
    "index": 10,
    "start_time": 18748,
    "text": "which I will explain in a minute,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 23216,
    "index": 11,
    "start_time": 20428,
    "text": "but less daylight \nactually causes color change."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 27206,
    "index": 12,
    "start_time": 23455,
    "text": "Most leaves contain chlorophyll,\na green pigment,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 30199,
    "index": 13,
    "start_time": 27207,
    "text": "that starts the process of photosynthesis."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 34569,
    "index": 14,
    "start_time": 30199,
    "text": "Chlorophyll helps convert sunlight, \ncarbon dioxide and water"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 37718,
    "index": 15,
    "start_time": 34569,
    "text": "into sugars that travel \nto the branches and the roots,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 39295,
    "index": 16,
    "start_time": 37718,
    "text": "feeding the tree."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 41616,
    "index": 17,
    "start_time": 39295,
    "text": "Chlorophyll breaks down and is replenished"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 43125,
    "index": 18,
    "start_time": 41616,
    "text": "all summer long."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 45091,
    "index": 19,
    "start_time": 43125,
    "text": "As daylight hours shorten, however,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 47290,
    "index": 20,
    "start_time": 45091,
    "text": "veins that bring water\nand nutrients to the leaf"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 49046,
    "index": 21,
    "start_time": 47290,
    "text": "gradually close off."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 51015,
    "index": 22,
    "start_time": 49046,
    "text": "The old chlorophyll disappears,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 53206,
    "index": 23,
    "start_time": 51015,
    "text": "and no new chlorophyll forms."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 55180,
    "index": 24,
    "start_time": 53206,
    "text": "The green color fades."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 57863,
    "index": 25,
    "start_time": 55180,
    "text": "Yellow and orange pigments,\nwhich were there all along,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 59253,
    "index": 26,
    "start_time": 57870,
    "text": "become visible."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 61454,
    "index": 27,
    "start_time": 59253,
    "text": "But, what about the red colors?"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 63850,
    "index": 28,
    "start_time": 61454,
    "text": "They actually form during the fall."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 66840,
    "index": 29,
    "start_time": 63850,
    "text": "As veins close, \nsugars get trapped in the leaf."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 70842,
    "index": 30,
    "start_time": 67199,
    "text": "They react with other chemicals\nto form the red pigments."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 74464,
    "index": 31,
    "start_time": 70874,
    "text": "You&#39;ll remember, I said intensity \nis connected to temperature."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 76962,
    "index": 32,
    "start_time": 74465,
    "text": "If days are bright, and nights are cold,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 78714,
    "index": 33,
    "start_time": 76962,
    "text": "more sugars get trapped,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 80727,
    "index": 34,
    "start_time": 78714,
    "text": "and the reds intensify."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 83282,
    "index": 35,
    "start_time": 80727,
    "text": "Eventually, the drier autumn weather"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 86416,
    "index": 36,
    "start_time": 83282,
    "text": "triggers a hormone telling \nthe tree to drop its leaves."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 89214,
    "index": 37,
    "start_time": 86416,
    "text": "Otherwise, the leaves would use up water"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 92919,
    "index": 38,
    "start_time": 89214,
    "text": "that the tree needs to keep \nits roots alive during the winter."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 95170,
    "index": 39,
    "start_time": 92919,
    "text": "Okay, what about evergreens?"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 99076,
    "index": 40,
    "start_time": 95171,
    "text": "The needles have a waxy coating,\nand less surface area,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 100761,
    "index": 41,
    "start_time": 99080,
    "text": "which reduces water loss."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 103470,
    "index": 42,
    "start_time": 101132,
    "text": "They also contain \na chemical like anti-freeze,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 106360,
    "index": 43,
    "start_time": 103470,
    "text": "so the roots and the leaves\ncan survive the winter."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 109520,
    "index": 44,
    "start_time": 106377,
    "text": "Now that you know the science\nbehind colorful autumn leaves,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 111460,
    "index": 45,
    "start_time": 109520,
    "text": "let&#39;s identify some of them:"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 113405,
    "index": 46,
    "start_time": 111460,
    "text": "oaks turn red and brown;"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 115518,
    "index": 47,
    "start_time": 113406,
    "text": "hickories turn bronze;"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 118655,
    "index": 48,
    "start_time": 115518,
    "text": "aspen and poplar turn gold and yellow;"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 121676,
    "index": 49,
    "start_time": 118655,
    "text": "sugar maples turn orange;"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 124354,
    "index": 50,
    "start_time": 121676,
    "text": "black maples turn yellow;"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 128300,
    "index": 51,
    "start_time": 124354,
    "text": "and red maples turn \n-- what else?-- brilliant red."
  },
  {
    "end_time": 131711,
    "index": 52,
    "start_time": 129205,
    "text": "For Scientific American&#39;s Instant Egghead,"
  },
  {
    "end_time": 133330,
    "index": 53,
    "start_time": 131711,
    "text": "I&#39;m Mark Fischetti."
  }
]